OL,6,F"You held a responsible and trusted
OL,7,Fposition in the finance department and
OL,8,Fwere trusted to handle large sums of
OL,9,Fmoney, and you used that position to
OL,10,Fdefraud your employer."
OL,12,FThe judge said it was "significant"
OL,13,Fthat the offending was "driven by a
OL,14,Fdesire to help your family who were
OL,15,Fstruggling".
OL,17,FShe added that Walsh had "strong
OL,18,Fpersonal mitigation" including no
OL,19,Fprior convictions and "genuine
OL,20,Fremorse".
