OL,6,FMitigating for Walsh, Joy Dykers said
OL,7,Fthe defendant had told her "none" of
OL,8,Fthe money was left and "it has all
OL,9,Fbeen spent", adding that some went on
OL,10,F"supporting her parents".
OL,12,FMs Dykers added: "A lot went on gifts
OL,13,Fand experiences for her family and
OL,14,Ffriends, trips to the theatre and
OL,15,Fholidays."
OL,17,FWalsh was also sentenced to up to 25
OL,18,Fdays of a rehabilitation activity
OL,19,Frequirement and 200 hours of unpaid
OL,20,Fwork in the community.
